\[\tan \theta = \frac{\sin \theta}{\cos \theta} = \frac{\sqrt{3} - 1}{\frac{\sqrt{6} + \sqrt{2}}{4}} = \frac{4 (\sqrt{3} - 1)}{\sqrt{6} + \sqrt{2}} = \frac{4 (\sqrt{3} - 1)(\sqrt{6} - \sqrt{2})}{(\sqrt{6} + \sqrt{2})(\sqrt{6} - \sqrt{2})} = \frac{4 (6 - \sqrt{18} - \sqrt{6} + \sqrt{2})}{4} = 6 - 3 \sqrt{2} - \sqrt{6} + \sqrt{2} = 6 - 2 \sqrt{2} - \sqrt{6}.\]Thus, $\theta = \arctan (6 - 2 \sqrt{2} - \sqrt{6}).$

